  "texts": [
    "The Breakpoint-based Chunker also made errors.",
    "It could, like the Fixed-size Chunker, group a sentence with a different chunk due to low semantic similarity with neighboring sentences, as seen with Sentence 4 being moved to Chunk 2.",
    "This shows the advantage of the joint distance measure in Equation 1, which prevented this error for the Clustering-based Chunker.",
    "Moreover, controlling chunk size was challenging; higher thresholds led to overly large chunks, while lower thresholds resulted in single-sentence chunks lacking contextual information, such as Chunk 4's meaningless \"Name binding\" phrase.",
    "Inspection on Normal Documents In Figure 7, the document about \"Interact Home Computer\" was naturally divided into four sections, though this structure was not provided to the chunkers."
